\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 #99 The Tiger in the Tobacco Pouch
\b0 \
\
1 Once there was a certain man.\
2 He was a tobacco-smoker.\
3 So he had all kinds of tobacco seedlings. [1]\
4 Well, he went looking for [a certain kind of] tobacco at a Shan\'92s.\
5 Then he said to the Shan, \'93Mister, don\'92t you have any \'9a\'fa \uc0\u596 \u768 -\u603 \u769 ?\'94[2]\
6 At this the Shan said, \'93What is this \'91\'9a\'fa \uc0\u596 \u768 -\u603 \u769 \'92?\'94 [3], so he repeated \'93\'9a\'fa \u596 \u768 -\u603 \u769 \'94.\
7 Then the Shan said to him,[4] \'93Oh! [5] In that case don\'92t up wrap it yet, don\'92t unwrap it yet!\
8 I\'92ll go look for a policeman first!\'94\
9 Then, since the Shan hadn\'92t understood, he unwrapped it and put it down [for him to see] \'97 he\'92d been talking about tobacco seedlings!\
\
